                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.F/124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-11T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. Your number 87, November 10, 6 p.m. Minister of Foreign Affairs informs me
                    that the Secretariat of the League of Nations was consulted concerning the
                    strictly mechanical preparations for the Conference and Rodriguez was anxious to
                    come to Habana to assist but … Cuban Government has refused to allow him to come
                    in any but a purely personal capacity. It has been absolutely impossible to find
                    any competent interpreters in Cuba and the League has therefore been asked
                    whether some of its interpreters could be obtained as individuals to serve
                    during the period of the Conference, subject to there being no objection on the
                    part of any other members of the Conference. He stated that no official of the
                    League had been invited to come to Cuba in any capacity whatsoever.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
